1
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:25,200
We can't run away from our feelings.

2
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:28,400
The best we can do is to accept them.

3
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,080
Though I'm just a taxi biker,

4
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,680
I'm better than a felon like you.

5
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:34,520
- Dammy!
- Dam!

6
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,280
I love dancing!

7
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,320
I am not letting you dance.

8
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,520
Dad!

9
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:41,960
You can't do this, Dad.
I need my shoes for the dance.

10
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:43,840
How will I dance now?

11
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:46,080
So quit dancing then! Go!

12
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:49,640
I want you to be more strict
when it comes to hiring new staff.

13
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,640
"Yes, for homicide."

14
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:54,000
Petch, are you out of your mind?

15
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,440
Do you want me to lie again?

16
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:58,960
You don't agree
with what Petch wrote, right?

17
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:02,360
Petch's record will be kept clean.

18
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:10,880
The Premium Nursing Home Project
that you sent me is interesting.

19
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:16,399
I would assign Piti and his team
to start with the project right away.

20
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,279
Can I set up a meeting for tomorrow?

21
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:20,120
<i>Of course, President.</i>

22
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:23,200
Also, inform the legal team
to join the meeting as well.

23
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:27,800
I need them to review the land contract
and the plan with us.

24
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:30,760
All right.

25
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,920
That's all for today.

26
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,320
Mom.

27
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,520
Where are you going?

28
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:41,600
I'm going to the Female Chief Executive
Officer Association meeting.

29
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:44,280
After that, I'm heading
to my friend's jewelry store opening.

30
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:47,200
I won't be here for dinner, darling.

31
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:48,560
I'll have dinner with my friends.

32
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,680
Have fun, darling.

33
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:50,920
Bye, honey.

34
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,480
Wait, Mom.

35
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:54,120
What is it, sweetie?

36
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,880
You're sick, Mom.

37
00:04:56,480 --> 00:05:00,240
You're attending online meetings
and social events.

38
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,320
Can your health take all of this?

39
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:04,560
I'm sick, but I'm not disabled, honey.

40
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:09,440
If your heart condition gets worse,
I'm afraid that you'll…

41
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:11,840
I'll be fine, sweetheart.

42
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:14,800
I have my medications.

43
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:17,160
And I have you, baby girl.

44
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:22,160
Your engagement with Ake
makes me very happy.

45
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:25,680
My heart condition won't get worse.

46
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:37,000
I'm looking forward to your wedding.

47
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:38,560
See you, dear.

48
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,920
Coffee, Ms. Dao.

49
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,000
Thank you.

50
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:59,200
Your mom loves pressuring people.
Are you okay with that?

51
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:02,040
I'm okay.

52
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,960
You're okay,
but what's with the long face?

53
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:08,600
I know you want to work
and gain more experience.

54
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,480
There's no need to rush the wedding.

55
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:13,520
I won't rush you like your mom.
I'll try to change her mind.

56
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,760
Really, Dad?

57
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,920
Really. There's no need to rush.

58
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,520
Your marriage to Ake is set in stone.

59
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,120
I know.

60
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,880
I have to marry Ake.

61
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:29,800
Is everything all right working with Ake?

62
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,440
I'm learning.

63
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:34,480
There's no problem except…

64
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,360
Except?

65
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:40,080
It's not a big problem.

66
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:43,600
I just want to improve
the atmosphere at work.

67
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:47,400
Tell me about it. I can be your advisor.

68
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:51,640
One of our employees is quite resistant.

69
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:55,640
He never takes my advice seriously.

70
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,840
He's arrogant
because he's talented, right?

71
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,320
How do you know?

72
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,880
He's really talented but arrogant.

73
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:05,400
Well, I'm a CEO.
I've encountered many kinds of people.

74
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:07,280
I have employees like that too.

75
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,760
So how do you deal with that?

76
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:11,280
First, you have to be patient.

77
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:16,120
It takes time and consistency

78
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,680
to change one's behavior.

79
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,120
What about the second?

80
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:26,560
Second, give him what he wants,
not what you want.

81
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:32,480
Give him what he wants, not what I want.

82
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,080
I'll consider that.

83
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:38,520
Thank you so much, Dad.

84
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:41,120
You're the best in the world.

85
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,760
You're just buttering me up.

86
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,480
I'm heading out to work then.

87
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,400
All right.

88
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:50,000
Win over the resistant team member.

89
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:15,240
If Dad knew
that the resistant employee was Petch,

90
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:18,040
he wouldn't be so kind to me.

91
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:27,120
Give him what he wants.

92
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,160
Hey! Where are you running away to? Hey!

93
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,440
Damn it.

94
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:36,080
Tell the debtor, Petch,
to pay the suit rental fee.

95
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:37,360
It has been too long!

96
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:38,880
Suit rental fee?

97
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,280
Petch owes Joke money?

98
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:59,080
Good morning.

99
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,640
Come on. We're here.

100
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,400
Yeah.

101
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,960
See you later, Dad.

102
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,120
Stay focused in class, son.

103
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,680
You must get the top score in class.

104
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:11,960
All right, Dad.

105
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,440
I'm heading back to work.

106
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:14,840
WATTHABANTHERNGTHAM SCHOOL

107
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:17,520
Hurry up or you'll be late
for the morning gathering.

108
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:19,960
Oh, dear!

109
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:22,320
Are you all right?

110
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,200
Are you all right?

111
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:26,440
Are you all right?

112
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:29,960
Are you hurt?

113
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:31,120
I'm all right.

114
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,360
PAPAYA SALAD, THAI HOT POT, THAI HOT POT

115
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,000
Dam.

116
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,120
For you, man.

117
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:45,080
You just read my mind.

118
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:51,600
Dam, have you seen my phone?

119
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:53,880
There. In the basket.

120
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,800
Where?

121
00:09:58,880 --> 00:09:59,720
What?

122
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,200
I NEED YOUR HELP
FOR A VERY IMPORTANT MATTER

123
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:05,640
CAN YOU COME AND SEE ME RIGHT NOW?

124
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:10,520
Don't tell me
that you haven't got rid of Petch by now.

125
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,520
I haven't, sir.

126
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,280
I understand that it's difficult.

127
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,400
Thank you for understanding.

128
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,960
The spy is on duty right now.

129
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,360
Do you want to go back
to your pathetic life?

130
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:41,000
Sir, I'm sorry.

131
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:42,760
Please give me another chance.

132
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,600
I gave you a chance

133
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,240
when you stole chips from the casino.

134
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:48,880
They wanted you dead.

135
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:51,720
If I hadn't stepped in,
you would be dead by now!

136
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:54,480
Sir, I know.

137
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:55,800
I'm incredibly grateful to you.

138
00:10:56,520 --> 00:10:59,520
Please at least consider
my loyalty to you.

139
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:03,240
Please give me another chance
to get rid of Petch.

140
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,480
Damn you!

141
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,160
Fine. You have another chance.

142
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,080
You have three days.

143
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,240
If you fail,

144
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,480
I won't go easy on you.

145
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:31,640
I admit that I was wrong,

146
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:34,200
but I'm turning over a new leaf.

147
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:36,480
I'll prove to everyone

148
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,200
that a man with a criminal record

149
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,920
can become a successful musician too.

150
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,040
Petch.

151
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,320
You won't make it.

152
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:48,360
Hey!

153
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,520
Hey! Stop there, you punk!

154
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:57,680
Watch where you're going!

155
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,920
How could you bump into a parked car?

156
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,880
I'm sorry. There was a man
walking across the street.

157
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,920
You're making excuses?

158
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:09,160
You look familiar.

159
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:11,760
You too.

160
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,080
You're Joe's sidekick!

161
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:16,600
You're Ake's right hand!

162
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,680
Good to see you today.

163
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:24,000
I need you to do me a favor.

164
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:26,520
What is it, brother?

165
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,160
Do you remember Petch?

166
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:34,280
I saw him yesterday.
He said he's a musician.

167
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:35,200
It's true.

168
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:37,200
He works at Ake's pub.

169
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:39,320
Really?

170
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:42,000
It's a long story.

171
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:43,920
Let's just say that Ake

172
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,160
wants to fire him quietly.

173
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:48,720
Nobody can blame Ake for that.

174
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:52,840
Which is why I would like
to ask you about the past.

175
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:54,920
Did Petch ever commit crimes in college?

176
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:58,400
Wait. Do you really not know?

177
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,360
Know what?

178
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:03,960
With that question,

179
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,840
it seems that you don't.

180
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,800
Just tell me already.

181
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:09,360
Well…

182
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:13,760
Something confidential
cannot be told for free.

183
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:16,360
I would like a payoff of about…

184
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,440
30,000 baht.

185
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:23,920
Money is not a problem.

186
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:25,960
Ake's got that covered.

187
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,680
But you can't make things up.

188
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,600
You need evidence.

189
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:34,000
No worries.
I have solid evidence for this.

190
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:35,520
Good.

191
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:37,200
Tomorrow,

192
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:40,440
bring all the evidence to Ake at the pub

193
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:42,640
and take your bribe.

194
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:44,960
Sure.

195
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:47,000
Petch will get fired tomorrow.

196
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,040
Petch.

197
00:13:57,920 --> 00:13:59,040
What's the matter?

198
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:00,680
Let's get inside.

199
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:02,520
TOPS OPEN EVERY DAY,
8 A.M. TO 10 P.M., FIRST FLOOR

200
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:09,400
BUY ONE GET ONE FREE

201
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:11,440
Why did you bring me here?

202
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:15,520
- Hi.
- Where is the men's suit section?

203
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,160
This way, ma'am.

204
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:18,600
Let's go.

205
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,240
Here, ma'am.

206
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:32,160
Petch, come take a look.

207
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:43,440
This one? A suit jacket fits you well.

208
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:46,160
The dark one looks cool on you.

209
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,280
But you can have a light-colored one too.

210
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:50,600
Excuse me?

211
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:52,200
- Yes?
- I would like to see that suit, please.

212
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,560
- All right, ma'am.
- No need.

213
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:58,320
Please take them back.
I won't try on any of them.

214
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:01,440
And you. We need to talk.

215
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,960
Petch. What the hell are you doing? Petch!

216
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,040
Petch. Let go of me.

217
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:08,960
Petch.

218
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:12,080
What the hell is wrong with you?

219
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:14,160
I should ask you that question.

220
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,840
What the hell are you doing?

221
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:18,320
- I see nothing wrong with buying a suit.
- Look.

222
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:20,600
You want me to try on some suits.

223
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:22,600
How is that an important matter?

224
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:24,400
If you have your own suits,

225
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:26,520
you don't have to rent them
from Joke anymore.

226
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,800
Look, Dao.

227
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:30,000
I can't afford those fine suits.

228
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:31,280
- Which is why--
- No need.

229
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:32,880
Don't buy them for me.

230
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,920
You can pay me back in installments.

231
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:37,960
Dao.

232
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:40,160
I don't want to bother you.

233
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:43,560
You could ask Joke for help,
but you can't ask me?

234
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:45,120
Are you applying a double standard?

235
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:46,920
Yes, I am.

236
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:47,920
Petch.

237
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:50,200
Let me tell you this.

238
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:53,600
I would rather let Joke
rip me off on the rent

239
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:58,160
than have you let me
pay in installments out of pity.

240
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:00,560
Petch.

241
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:02,640
You're being blinded by pride.

242
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:03,680
Petch!

243
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,800
They're all cool.

244
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:13,400
I wish I had a pair.

245
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,120
What?

246
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:22,520
Why are they so expensive?

247
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,840
Would you like some shoes, boy?

248
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:27,320
Yes, but I don't have enough money.

249
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,000
I can buy them for you.

250
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:32,160
- Really?
- Of course. But…

251
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:34,120
Can you come to the toilet with me?

252
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,720
What for?

253
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:37,920
I don't know where it is.
Can you help me find it?

254
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:40,320
- I can't.
- Why not?

255
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,880
You're being too friendly.

256
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:42,920
Smart kid.

257
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:47,480
You just met me,
but you know how friendly I am.

258
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:51,160
With that look and that over-friendliness,
it seems like…

259
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:53,680
It seems like what, boy?

260
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:55,160
You're looking to groom a kid!

261
00:16:57,760 --> 00:16:58,640
Petch, stop.

262
00:16:58,720 --> 00:16:59,960
We need to talk.

263
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:01,560
Petch.

264
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:04,640
You can't keep walking away from me.

265
00:17:05,599 --> 00:17:07,079
I have nothing to say to you.

266
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,000
Petch.

267
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:09,480
Petch. Don't be like this.

268
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:12,200
Be careful, kid.

269
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,800
Help me!

270
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:14,760
What's going on?

271
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:18,280
That man was trying to take me with him.

272
00:17:18,359 --> 00:17:20,359
What? The kid is making things up.

273
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:24,800
He said he would buy me shoes
if I went to the toilet with him.

274
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:28,600
You're evil. Did you try to harass him?

275
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,320
I don't know what you're talking about.

276
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:32,600
Where are you going?
I'll take you to the police!

277
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,320
Please don't tell the police.

278
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:36,080
Why?

279
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,280
Exactly.

280
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,240
Why not?

281
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:39,600
I…

282
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:43,000
I skipped school to be here.
My dad will beat me if he finds out.

283
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:44,880
I'm begging you.

284
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:47,240
Please don't tell the police.

285
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:49,400
Please have mercy on me.

286
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:56,200
We should forget our war
and help the boy first.

287
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:01,920
Kid.

288
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:03,280
Look.

289
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:07,520
You're lucky that you know
the moves of an abuser.

290
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:10,320
I read the news online.

291
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,720
He did it exactly like in the news.

292
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,040
But

293
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:18,360
if you don't tell the police,

294
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:21,120
I'll have to interrogate you.

295
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:23,200
Interrogate?

296
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:26,560
Like, "Who are your parents?"

297
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:27,760
"Where do you live?"

298
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:04,880
ONE DEAD IN TEEN BRAWL

299
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,720
I'll destroy you, Petch.

300
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:09,360
Tomorrow is your doomsday.

301
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:14,760
Is it tasty?

302
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:16,640
Very tasty.

303
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:19,560
Thank you both
for treating me to ice cream.

304
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:21,800
I feel much better.

305
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:24,320
But promise me one thing.

306
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:27,720
Promise me
that you won't skip school again.

307
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:31,760
I promise,
even if my dad burns all my shoes,

308
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:34,480
that I will not skip school again.

309
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:37,680
Are you mad at your dad?

310
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:39,800
Not at all.

311
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:42,920
It burdens him enough
to work and raise me.

312
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,720
How could I be mad at him?

313
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:46,320
I love him.

314
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:49,520
But I don't know if he loves me or not.

315
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:56,200
Shogun.

316
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,880
Every father loves their children.

317
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:02,840
Do you really mean that?

318
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:04,520
I mean it.

319
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,520
You just had a misunderstanding.

320
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:13,400
So how about we take you home?

321
00:20:14,040 --> 00:20:16,840
Then, we'll talk to your dad.

322
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:19,240
You two are very kind.

323
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:22,520
Thank you very much, both of you.

324
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:23,680
No problem.

325
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:26,360
Are you ready to go?

326
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:27,400
Wait.

327
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:30,560
Can I ask you two one thing?

328
00:20:31,160 --> 00:20:33,160
Fine. Go ahead.

329
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:36,960
Are you two

330
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:40,640
boyfriend and girlfriend?

331
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:42,600
- We're not, Shogun!
- We're not, Shogun!

332
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:47,120
- We're not.
- We're not.

333
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:52,160
How cute. You two speak at the same time.

334
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:58,000
That's how couples are at my school.

335
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:00,640
Shogun, that's enough, kid.
You're talking nonsense.

336
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:02,240
Don't say that.

337
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:05,040
You're embarrassing Dao.

338
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:07,520
No, I'm not embarrassed.

339
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,000
I'm not good enough.

340
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:10,840
I'm the one who's embarrassing him.

341
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:15,520
I'm totally confused.
What are you two talking about?

342
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:17,360
I don't understand.

343
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:26,320
WATTHABANTHERNGTHAM SCHOOL

344
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:29,040
Goodbye. Get home safely.

345
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:30,640
Take care of your little sister.

346
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:35,680
Miss. Have you seen my son, Shogun?

347
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,560
Shogun didn't come to class.

348
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:38,760
What?

349
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:41,560
I sent him here this morning.
How could he be absent?

350
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,760
Shogun really didn't come to class today.

351
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:47,160
I thought he was sick.

352
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:48,840
You cheeky monkey.

353
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:50,720
You cause me trouble again.

354
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,640
Take it easy, sir.

355
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:54,560
I'll help look for him.

356
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:56,520
Stay out of this. I'll find him myself.

357
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:30,520
This is my house.

358
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:32,000
Here?

359
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:33,760
Thank you so much.

360
00:22:33,840 --> 00:22:36,840
You had to park far and walk me here.

361
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:38,760
That's all right.

362
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:41,240
Only you and your dad live here?

363
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:45,400
Yes. Since my grandma passed away,
it has just been the two of us.

364
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:46,720
What about your mom?

365
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:53,520
Dad said Mom left me with him
the moment I was born.

366
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:57,360
My dad was still in college then.

367
00:22:57,440 --> 00:23:00,480
Grandma was the one who raised me,

368
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:04,800
but she passed away last year.

369
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,960
Your dad might be the same age as me.

370
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:07,880
Yes.

371
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:10,040
I think I can talk to him.

372
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,680
- Dad!
- Shogun.

373
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:20,560
You…

374
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:22,440
What are you doing here at my house?

375
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:23,880
Bank?

376
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,600
You are Shogun's dad?

377
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:28,480
That's right!

378
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:31,920
Oh, wow. Did you know Petch from before?

379
00:23:32,520 --> 00:23:34,760
Your dad and I went to the same college.

380
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:36,800
You skipped some details.

381
00:23:37,560 --> 00:23:39,000
We went to the same college,

382
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:40,960
but we were not friends.

383
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:42,440
We were rivals.

384
00:23:42,520 --> 00:23:44,600
I don't care what you think of me.

385
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:47,080
But as for Shogun,

386
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:50,280
he should do what he likes.

387
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:52,840
Not what you like.

388
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,800
You really don't know your place.

389
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:58,320
You kidnapped my son

390
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:01,080
and now you're lecturing me?

391
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:02,040
Dad.

392
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:03,840
You've got him wrong.

393
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:06,520
Petch didn't kidnap me.

394
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:10,720
Petch saved me from a child abuser.

395
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:11,640
Hey!

396
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:13,440
Are you backing him up?

397
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:14,960
- Quiet or I'll beat you.
- Hey.

398
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:16,880
You shouldn't hit a child.

399
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:18,920
Auntie.

400
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:21,760
Keep your nose out of my business.

401
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,640
Did you just call me auntie?

402
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:26,280
Dao, calm down.

403
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:31,640
Dao?

404
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:39,040
I remember now.

405
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,000
It's you.

406
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:44,840
Ms. Natedao, Akekaphol's woman.

407
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:46,600
That's nonsense.

408
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:48,480
I'm not anyone's woman.

409
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:50,760
Stop lying.

410
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:54,120
No matter how many years have passed,

411
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:58,520
Ms. Natedao still runs away
from Akekaphol to have fun with Petch.

412
00:24:58,600 --> 00:24:59,960
If you don't want to get hurt,

413
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:01,520
shut up.

414
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:04,160
Petch.

415
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:06,600
Don't. He isn't worth it.

416
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,200
Petch, are you all right?

417
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:16,640
Dad!

418
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:18,720
Why did you hit Petch?

419
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:20,400
You're mean!

420
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:22,800
Stay out of this or you'll be next!

421
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:27,440
You two care so much for each other.

422
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:31,600
I suppose Natedao doesn't know about it.

423
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,680
About what?

424
00:25:35,360 --> 00:25:36,680
The truth

425
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:38,640
that he was sent to juvie.

426
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,000
How is that?

427
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:42,960
I've known for a while.

428
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:44,240
You have?

429
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:47,760
You still hang out with him?

430
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:48,680
Why not?

431
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:53,840
A man from juvie like Petch
saved your son from danger.

432
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:58,520
Who asked you to?

433
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:00,920
I don't owe you anything.

434
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,960
I can't change your mind.

435
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:04,840
But if you ask me,

436
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:09,120
Petch is way kinder and more generous
than someone with a clean record like you.

437
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,040
Enough.

438
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:11,920
I won't hear another word.

439
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:16,480
Just get back to where you two came from

440
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:18,800
and leave my son alone!

441
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:21,280
Otherwise, I'll sue both of you.

442
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:24,360
Get inside.

443
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:37,120
I'm worried about Shogun.

444
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:40,080
I believe that they love each other.

445
00:26:41,560 --> 00:26:43,800
But it takes time
to understand each other.

446
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:46,040
Exactly.

447
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:48,760
I just can't get Shogun out of my mind.

448
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:52,040
Don't worry, auntie.

449
00:26:52,120 --> 00:26:52,960
Hey.

450
00:26:53,040 --> 00:26:53,960
Did you call me auntie?

451
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:55,880
The word "auntie" is so powerful.

452
00:26:57,080 --> 00:26:59,120
A simple word that does a lot of damage.

453
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:00,920
Are you mocking me?

454
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:03,280
- Are you mocking me?
- Dao.

455
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:06,880
I saw you were stressed.
I was just teasing you.

456
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:08,800
Teasing me?

457
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:10,520
It's my turn to tease you!

458
00:27:11,120 --> 00:27:11,960
Oh, no!

459
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,680
Why are you blushing?

460
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:32,560
Do you have a fever?

461
00:27:32,640 --> 00:27:34,240
Are you out of your mind?

462
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:37,720
Don't call me auntie again
or you'll be dead!

463
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:47,920
Why am I blushing?

464
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:50,040
I was trying to keep my cool.

465
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,480
Dao.

466
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:53,840
Dao.

467
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:55,560
What do you want this time?

468
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,000
No.

469
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:59,600
You always assume the worst of me.

470
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:03,200
Because I don't know which mood you're in.

471
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:05,080
We already took Shogun home,

472
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:08,000
but I don't know if you'll keep nagging
about the suits or not.

473
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:10,120
Of course I will.

474
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,520
It's like you can read my mind.

475
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:16,200
Do you want to start a fight?

476
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:19,720
I admit it.

477
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:23,360
I admit that I can be a hothead.

478
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:26,280
But now, I'm ready to explain it to you.

479
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:28,880
I'm all ears.

480
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:35,640
I get it now that it's better to get help.

481
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:40,120
But I don't want to be dependent on you.

482
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:43,720
Aren't you overestimating the situation?

483
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:45,720
Better not underestimate it.

484
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:51,720
I'm a man and a man must strive.

485
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:54,240
I must rely on myself.

486
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:58,480
That's what a man should do.

487
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:01,000
But isn't it heavy?

488
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:04,760
What is heavy?

489
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,160
The pride that burdens your soul.

490
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:10,560
Isn't it heavy?

491
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:16,720
But pride

492
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,440
hurts less than love.

493
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:27,400
No matter how heavy it is,

494
00:29:28,520 --> 00:29:29,640
at the end of the day,

495
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:34,600
I want the person I love
to be proud of me.

496
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:39,560
And I want them to understand

497
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:42,040
that I really need them

498
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:44,280
to be proud of me.

499
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:47,760
That's why I must earn it.

500
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:10,120
You ungrateful kid.

501
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:16,400
I work to send you to school,
not to hang out with Petch!

502
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:17,920
No, I didn't.

503
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,640
I didn't hang out with Petch.

504
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:20,560
Shut up!

505
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:22,200
Don't talk back to me.

506
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:26,800
You'd better be reasonable.

507
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:28,240
Reasonable?

508
00:30:29,040 --> 00:30:30,240
Reasonable?

509
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,160
Listen carefully, Shogun.

510
00:30:43,320 --> 00:30:45,960
If you insist on hanging out with Petch,

511
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:48,680
you're no longer my son.

512
00:30:49,360 --> 00:30:51,480
And I won't give a damn
whether you live or die!

513
00:31:13,760 --> 00:31:15,040
Oh, there you are, honey.

514
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:17,520
I'm expecting you for dinner.

515
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:18,920
Oh, Dad.

516
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:20,880
You shouldn't have waited for me.

517
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:23,440
It's okay. I just want to chat
and have dinner with you.

518
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:25,480
I want to know
about the resistant employee too.

519
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:26,600
Did you win him over?

520
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:31,120
What's with the silence?

521
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:32,520
Is everything all right?

522
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:36,360
No, I didn't win him over.

523
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:37,280
Oh, dear.

524
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:40,760
I thought no one could ever change him.

525
00:31:41,280 --> 00:31:44,920
But after what happened today,
I understand him more.

526
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:49,040
I'm home.

527
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:51,600
You're back early.

528
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:55,600
You sound like you don't want to see me.

529
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:57,120
I didn't mean it that way.

530
00:31:57,200 --> 00:31:59,600
You said you would have dinner
with your friends.

531
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:04,480
Joom, the owner of the jewelry store,
had something urgent come up,

532
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:06,240
so we canceled dinner.

533
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:08,280
So,

534
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:13,120
have you two been gossiping about me?

535
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,960
Who would dare talk behind your back?

536
00:32:16,040 --> 00:32:18,720
I was asking her about her employee.

537
00:32:18,800 --> 00:32:19,640
Oh, I see.

538
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:24,240
I don't think you should let
one employee at work burden your brain.

539
00:32:24,320 --> 00:32:28,040
You should think like a CEO. Like Ake.

540
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:32,200
What's interesting about Ake?

541
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:35,280
Dear, why are you saying that?

542
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:38,160
Ake is your fiancé, honey.

543
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:40,280
Yes, I know.

544
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:43,880
I got engaged to Ake because of you.

545
00:32:43,960 --> 00:32:45,840
That's all I know.

546
00:32:49,280 --> 00:32:50,520
Dao.

547
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:52,640
Dao.

548
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:54,880
Are you saying
that I forced you into this?

549
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:57,840
Didn't you force her though?

550
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:59,880
Honey.

551
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:04,360
You agreed with me, didn't you?

552
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:06,960
Why are you blaming me now?

553
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:09,600
I'm on your side.

554
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:13,040
Honestly, Dao has been going
really easy on you lately.

555
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:15,160
So you should cut her some slack too.

556
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:17,600
Is that so?

557
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:20,040
They're gone.

558
00:33:23,040 --> 00:33:25,400
I don't like how they talk at all.

559
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:29,120
I should call Ake.

560
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:43,200
Who the hell is calling me at this moment?

561
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:51,440
Hello, ma'am.

562
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,520
I was just thinking about you.

563
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:56,640
That's sweet.
But why haven't I heard from you?

564
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:58,960
You never visit me for dinner.

565
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:03,360
Ma'am, I've been quite busy recently.

566
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:05,320
Right now, I…

567
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:08,199
I don't sleep at home these days.

568
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:10,600
Oh, you're such a hardworking man.

569
00:34:10,679 --> 00:34:13,679
Dao is the luckiest girl to have you.

570
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:16,760
- Hey!
<i>- What was that?</i>

571
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:18,360
I…

572
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:20,639
Ma'am, I was…

573
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:25,719
watching the promo clip
without turning the sound off.

574
00:34:26,920 --> 00:34:29,199
Ma'am, I should get back to work now.

575
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:32,080
Please take care of yourself, ma'am.

576
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:34,520
All right, I will.

577
00:34:38,719 --> 00:34:42,120
This son-in-law-to-be never fails me.

578
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:49,040
Dao, one day, you'll thank me
for choosing this man for you.

579
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:53,239
Such bad timing.

580
00:34:57,960 --> 00:35:00,400
No auntie will interrupt us anymore, baby.

581
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,720
Let me have it my way, baby.

582
00:35:07,600 --> 00:35:09,920
- Sir.
- Mud!

583
00:35:10,520 --> 00:35:11,520
Why are you here?

584
00:35:11,600 --> 00:35:13,400
Do you want to lose your job?

585
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:15,720
Sir, you see…

586
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:17,680
I found a way to get rid of Petch.

587
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:21,520
What?

588
00:35:22,040 --> 00:35:24,680
I found someone who could expose Petch.

589
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:26,480
Ake.

590
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:28,520
Would you make him leave now?

591
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:30,160
You're the one who should leave!

592
00:35:31,360 --> 00:35:33,280
Ake.

593
00:35:34,680 --> 00:35:37,160
Will you leave
or do I have to drag you out?

594
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:39,520
Ake.

595
00:35:40,560 --> 00:35:43,520
Leave. You're annoying.

596
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:49,520
Mud.

597
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:51,480
Tell me about it.

598
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:54,000
All right, sir.

599
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:57,640
Remember those mechanic students
who fought Petch?

600
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:01,200
Yes. Why?

601
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:03,600
I met one of them, Bank.

602
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:07,880
Bank has evidence to make Petch leave.

603
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:13,880
Evidence of what?

604
00:36:15,520 --> 00:36:17,040
Please wait until tomorrow.

605
00:36:17,120 --> 00:36:20,120
I'll bring him to you.

606
00:36:21,560 --> 00:36:23,200
Don't disappoint me.

607
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:25,920
I hope tomorrow

608
00:36:26,680 --> 00:36:29,200
is Petch's last day here.

609
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:01,400
Petch. Why are you here?

610
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,960
Are you going to buy the shoes for Shogun?

611
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:10,840
Are you going to

612
00:37:11,360 --> 00:37:13,320
buy this pair too?

613
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:37,440
Shogun.

614
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:39,720
I made you a fried egg.

615
00:37:40,600 --> 00:37:41,960
Get up and eat some.

616
00:37:42,040 --> 00:37:43,600
I'm heading out for work.

617
00:37:48,680 --> 00:37:49,800
Hey.

618
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:54,040
It's the weekend,
but you still have to read your textbooks.

619
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:57,680
No dancing, no going out.

620
00:37:58,200 --> 00:37:59,280
Don't you try me.

621
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:26,800
Shogun would be over the moon
to receive these shoes as a present.

622
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:28,880
I'm happy for him too.

623
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:31,360
But as for Bank,

624
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:33,840
I don't know what he would say.

625
00:38:34,680 --> 00:38:36,440
Have you ever given up that easily?

626
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:44,840
I believe that no matter how hard it gets,

627
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:48,000
you'll win Bank over for sure.

628
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:50,040
Hey.

629
00:38:51,080 --> 00:38:52,400
You're buttering me up.

630
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:55,720
I'm not buying it.

631
00:38:58,480 --> 00:39:02,280
We'll see.
Your words always go against your heart.

632
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:08,920
Shogun.

633
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:11,720
Are you home, Shogun?

634
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:16,600
No one is answering.

635
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:17,880
Maybe they're not home.

636
00:39:22,040 --> 00:39:23,600
Shogun's school shoes are here.

637
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:41,280
The door is unlocked.

638
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:44,040
You should take a look inside.

639
00:39:51,120 --> 00:39:52,280
Shogun?

640
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:53,680
Shogun?

641
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:55,120
Shogun?

642
00:39:58,960 --> 00:40:00,080
Are you home?

643
00:40:03,440 --> 00:40:04,520
Shogun?

644
00:40:21,280 --> 00:40:22,640
I don't think he's here.

645
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:25,240
This is not our lucky day.

646
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:43,280
- Shogun.
- Shogun.

647
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:45,000
Shogun.

648
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:53,200
He's burning up.

649
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:55,760
Petch.

650
00:40:58,120 --> 00:40:59,800
- What?
- He's injured.

651
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:06,280
I'll take him to the hospital.

652
00:41:06,360 --> 00:41:09,200
No. We should call the doctor here.
I'll take care of it.

653
00:41:13,560 --> 00:41:15,640
Ake is expecting to see you at three.

654
00:41:15,720 --> 00:41:17,400
<i>All right. I'll be there.</i>

655
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:20,000
About your evidence…

656
00:41:20,640 --> 00:41:21,680
It's the real deal, right?

657
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:23,480
Come on.

658
00:41:23,560 --> 00:41:26,920
I wouldn't have offered it to you
if it wasn't.

659
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:30,720
Besides, Akekaphol
isn't the only one who hates Petch.

660
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:33,680
I've despised him for ages.

661
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:38,360
I can't wait to see Akekaphol
get rid of Petch.

662
00:41:39,240 --> 00:41:40,800
It might kill his arrogance.

663
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:44,600
You have such determination.
Akekaphol is going to like you.

664
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:48,880
<i>Akekaphol can pay me extra if he wants.</i>

665
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:51,720
I'm kidding,
but you can take it seriously.

666
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:54,880
All right. See you then.

667
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:58,320
Petch.

668
00:41:59,160 --> 00:42:01,440
Today is your doomsday.

669
00:42:04,280 --> 00:42:05,480
Hey, Bank.

670
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:06,960
What's up, bro?

671
00:42:07,560 --> 00:42:09,480
I passed by your neighborhood.

672
00:42:09,560 --> 00:42:10,840
- People are--
- Bro.

673
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:12,840
I don't want to hear
gossip about neighbors.

674
00:42:12,920 --> 00:42:15,680
Not about the neighbors. It's your son.

675
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:17,280
What?

676
00:42:17,360 --> 00:42:20,520
They said he's in bad condition.
You should go home to your son.

677
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:22,200
Shogun.

678
00:42:31,960 --> 00:42:34,920
I've cleaned and dressed the wound
and given him an antibiotic injection.

679
00:42:36,280 --> 00:42:38,720
Make sure he rests a lot.

680
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:40,400
And don't get the wound wet.

681
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:42,440
All right, doctor.

682
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:45,400
I'll prescribe him
an antibiotic and a painkiller.

683
00:42:45,920 --> 00:42:48,120
Make sure he takes them as prescribed.

684
00:42:48,720 --> 00:42:50,640
All right. Thank you so much.

685
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:57,400
Bank. You finally came.

686
00:42:59,400 --> 00:43:00,480
This is my house.

687
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:02,280
Why are people crowding here?

688
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:05,680
Shogun has a terrible fever.
He might not survive this.

689
00:43:05,760 --> 00:43:08,320
Hey. Watch your tongue.

690
00:43:09,240 --> 00:43:10,600
- Move!
- What's wrong with him?

691
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:15,520
Petch.

692
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:17,480
Did you break into my house?

693
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:21,600
I'll call the police.

694
00:43:21,680 --> 00:43:24,640
How could they arrest
the person who saved your son's life?

695
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:28,040
What? What are you talking about?

696
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:33,560
Your son was cut
by a piece of mirror or glass.

697
00:43:34,160 --> 00:43:35,920
His wound was left untreated.

698
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:38,440
The wound got infected,
causing a high fever.

699
00:43:38,960 --> 00:43:42,120
You're lucky to have good friends.

700
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:44,760
They called me to treat your son in time.

701
00:43:45,360 --> 00:43:46,480
Otherwise,

702
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:49,080
he could have had a seizure and died.

703
00:43:51,040 --> 00:43:52,600
How is he doing right now?

704
00:43:53,200 --> 00:43:56,960
His fever has gone down,
but he should be monitored.

705
00:43:57,760 --> 00:44:01,440
If something bad happens,
please call me immediately.

706
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:04,280
All right.

707
00:44:05,760 --> 00:44:08,800
If there is nothing else,
I'll be on my way.

708
00:44:09,760 --> 00:44:11,920
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

709
00:44:21,840 --> 00:44:23,960
Just set our conflict aside

710
00:44:25,120 --> 00:44:26,480
and check on Shogun.

711
00:44:30,800 --> 00:44:31,840
Shogun.

712
00:44:32,360 --> 00:44:33,240
Shogun.

713
00:44:43,200 --> 00:44:44,240
Shogun.

714
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:47,200
How are you doing, son?

715
00:44:48,720 --> 00:44:49,760
But…

716
00:44:50,360 --> 00:44:51,840
How did you get this wound?

717
00:44:53,040 --> 00:44:54,760
I want to ask you too.

718
00:44:57,120 --> 00:45:00,000
The doctor said
the wound was caused by a sharp object.

719
00:45:00,080 --> 00:45:01,960
A piece of mirror or a piece of glass.

720
00:45:02,840 --> 00:45:04,120
So I want to ask you.

721
00:45:05,280 --> 00:45:06,880
Did something happen yesterday?

722
00:45:07,400 --> 00:45:08,760
How did he get injured?

723
00:45:32,840 --> 00:45:36,040
I let you down…

724
00:45:38,440 --> 00:45:40,000
so I…

725
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:46,360
Oh, my son.

726
00:45:53,840 --> 00:45:54,720
Bank.

727
00:46:01,800 --> 00:46:02,920
Bank, you idiot!

728
00:46:03,440 --> 00:46:04,600
You're evil!

729
00:46:10,000 --> 00:46:11,840
You hurt Shogun!

730
00:46:27,960 --> 00:46:30,440
Bank, you're evil.

731
00:46:30,520 --> 00:46:31,920
You hurt your own son.

732
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:35,280
I'm an evil dad.

733
00:46:35,360 --> 00:46:36,800
I'll make it up to you, Shogun.

734
00:46:38,200 --> 00:46:39,680
Bank!

735
00:46:39,760 --> 00:46:40,800
Stop! Put it down!

736
00:46:40,880 --> 00:46:41,880
- Get off!
- Stop!

737
00:46:41,960 --> 00:46:44,960
- Bank! Put it down!
- Get off me!

738
00:46:45,680 --> 00:46:47,640
Enough. Bank, listen.

739
00:46:49,520 --> 00:46:51,520
Will this help Shogun get better?

740
00:46:52,640 --> 00:46:54,160
What else can I do?

741
00:46:54,680 --> 00:46:56,680
I hurt Shogun!

742
00:46:57,800 --> 00:47:02,360
Then find ways to make him happy
instead of hurting yourself.

743
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:05,040
What do you want me to do?

744
00:47:05,640 --> 00:47:07,200
Nothing, Bank.

745
00:47:07,720 --> 00:47:09,040
Hey, listen to me.

746
00:47:10,480 --> 00:47:11,880
Just open up your mind

747
00:47:12,800 --> 00:47:15,600
and accept Shogun as he is.

748
00:47:17,080 --> 00:47:17,960
Open up my mind?

749
00:47:19,800 --> 00:47:20,800
Yes.

750
00:47:22,360 --> 00:47:23,200
Bank.

751
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:26,280
I know you love your son.

752
00:47:27,360 --> 00:47:29,360
Too much expectation
only brings you misery.

753
00:47:31,320 --> 00:47:35,000
You should accept what Shogun does
and who he is.

754
00:47:36,440 --> 00:47:38,400
That will make Shogun happy.

755
00:47:43,480 --> 00:47:44,360
So?

756
00:47:45,600 --> 00:47:46,840
Do you agree with me?

757
00:47:53,640 --> 00:47:54,920
You're right.

758
00:47:58,600 --> 00:48:00,280
I didn't even finish school.

759
00:48:01,920 --> 00:48:03,400
I was a teenage dad.

760
00:48:07,480 --> 00:48:10,160
I put all my dreams on his shoulders.

761
00:48:19,040 --> 00:48:20,440
I was selfish.

762
00:48:24,440 --> 00:48:25,280
Good.

763
00:48:28,760 --> 00:48:29,600
Bank.

764
00:48:30,400 --> 00:48:32,160
When you come to your senses,

765
00:48:33,880 --> 00:48:35,640
you will love Shogun as he is.

766
00:48:38,120 --> 00:48:39,920
That won't just make him happy.

767
00:48:41,400 --> 00:48:42,760
It will make you happy too.

768
00:48:44,320 --> 00:48:45,680
You will be happy too.

769
00:48:50,840 --> 00:48:51,960
In my life,

770
00:48:52,480 --> 00:48:54,240
nothing matters like Shogun.

771
00:48:57,240 --> 00:48:59,720
I'll fix myself for Shogun.

772
00:49:06,160 --> 00:49:07,000
Good.

773
00:49:12,360 --> 00:49:14,040
I have a call. Give me a minute.

774
00:49:16,960 --> 00:49:18,920
What's up, Dam?

775
00:49:21,640 --> 00:49:23,280
You don't have to ask where I am.

776
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:24,960
I'll see you there.

777
00:49:28,360 --> 00:49:29,560
Dam called me.

778
00:49:30,720 --> 00:49:32,480
We're learning the songs for our gig.

779
00:49:35,800 --> 00:49:36,800
See you, Bank.

780
00:49:40,280 --> 00:49:41,480
Dao, let's go.

781
00:49:57,880 --> 00:49:59,120
I'm sorry, Petch.

782
00:50:00,920 --> 00:50:03,280
I have to do what you never expected.

783
00:50:04,840 --> 00:50:05,840
NEXT EPISODE

784
00:50:06,560 --> 00:50:07,520
Oh, no!

785
00:50:07,600 --> 00:50:08,720
Damn you!

786
00:50:10,440 --> 00:50:11,680
- Get out of here.
- Try me.

787
00:50:11,760 --> 00:50:13,120
A lowlife like you…

788
00:50:15,120 --> 00:50:16,920
shouldn't bring Dao down to his level.

789
00:50:17,000 --> 00:50:18,000
Leave.

790
00:50:18,520 --> 00:50:20,640
I'll pay you double.

791
00:50:20,720 --> 00:50:23,200
Someone was about to tell Ake
about Petch being in juvie.

792
00:50:23,280 --> 00:50:24,360
What?

793
00:50:24,440 --> 00:50:25,800
I'm expecting to see you.

794
00:50:29,120 --> 00:50:30,120
Bank.

795
00:50:30,720 --> 00:50:33,160
Nice to see you again, buddy.

796
00:50:47,320 --> 00:50:52,560
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

797
00:50:53,560 --> 00:50:58,520
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

798
00:50:59,360 --> 00:51:05,320
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

799
00:51:05,400 --> 00:51:10,240
<i>But never reaching you</i>

800
00:51:11,440 --> 00:51:16,320
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

801
00:51:17,640 --> 00:51:22,320
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

802
00:51:23,960 --> 00:51:29,120
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

803
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:35,160
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

804
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:40,720
<i>You are out of reach</i>

805
00:51:41,560 --> 00:51:47,000
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

806
00:51:48,600 --> 00:51:53,320
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

807
00:51:53,400 --> 00:51:58,560
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

808
00:51:59,560 --> 00:52:03,800
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

809
00:52:05,680 --> 00:52:10,280
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

810
00:52:11,640 --> 00:52:17,240
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

811
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:23,320
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

812
00:52:23,400 --> 00:52:24,840
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
